      "rationale": "A two-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse and medium grids). GCI on area-averaged wall shear stress was 7.2%, marginally exceeding the 5% threshold. The assessment team judged the shortfall negligible given the conservative hemolysis model coefficients, and the factor was recorded as Gradation 1. The decision record accepts the model at Medium assurance despite this one-step shortfall."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
